chapters.title: Male health initiatives get less money than those aimed at women

description:
Starting to think this Sargon of Akkad fellow doesn't much care for feminism.

Video Sources:

Sargon's #Feminists4Autism video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SMWUrJdR9FA

Sargon defending Elliot Rodger: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2Am5fd_Zpws

He was responding to a video by  'lacigreen': https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HPFcspwbrq8&bpctr=1475446921

Featured video from Steve Shives:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DtH12yILQvY

Special appearance by LeafyIsHere

Text Sources:

Health initiative funding: https://www.thebureauinvestigates.com/2012/06/25/male-health-initiatives-get-less-money-than-those-aimed-at-women/

Suicide rate: https://www.theguardian.com/society/2014/feb/18/male-suicides-three-times-women-samaritans-bristol

Homelessness:
Telegraph: http://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/11787304/Homelessness-is-a-gendered-issue-and-it-mostly-impacts-men.html

Guardian: https://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/aug/05/more-homeless-women-use-heroine-and-cocaine-than-men-study-finds

Homeless Link: http://www.homeless.org.uk/our-work/resources/homeless-health-needs-audit

Autism in women under-diagnosed:

http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-37221030

HuffPo article on autism in girls:

http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/autism-girls-study_us_55e9b2fce4b03784e275a2c0

https://feminismandreligion.com/2015/06/16/autism-a-feminist-issue-by-esther-nelson/
